title: An act to amend Section 3068 of the Civil Code, relating to vehicle liens.
content: Existing law grants a person a lien on a vehicle, dependent upon possession, for the compensation connected with repairing, furnishing supplies, storing, or renting parking space for that vehicle. Existing law establishes how the lien arises and how it may be extinguished. This bill would make a nonsubstantive change in these provisions.
